Abstract = {Wetlands are unique ecosystems formed by the interaction between land
   and water on Earth. Poyang Lake, which is a part of China's largest
   freshwater lake wetland, is well known for its ecological and economic
   importance. This study uses a social-ecological system (SES) framework
