Month = {MAY 19},
Abstract = {Lakes in the Indian city of Bangalore face conservation challenges. In
   order to analyse these conservation challenges, the article uses
   DiGaetano and Strom's framework on urban governance to identify and
   analyse the different modes of lake governance which are at play within
   the city. Using data from semi-structured interviews and secondary
   research, this research argues that three modes of governance
   (managerial, clientelist and populist) characterize the city's lake
   system. Conflict amongst these modes of governance, which often act at
   cross-purposes to each other, may be one of the reasons why Bangalore
   has been unable to protect its lakes.},
